{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-11-09","name":"Jordan Champernon","nameForms":[{"lang":"und","fullText":"Jordan Champernon","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Jordan"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Champernon"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Campo Arnulfi","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1096–1190","fullLifespan":"1096–1190","birthDate":"+1096","birthPlace":{"address":"Cambernon, Manche, Normandy, France, ","geo":{"latitude":49.081,"longitude":-1.3854,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1190","deathPlace":{"address":", Devon, , England","geo":{"latitude":50.73646,"longitude":-3.71887,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nJORDAN de CHAMBERNUN. Seigneur de Cambernon and Maisoncelles in Normandy, France. In 1146 Jordan de Campo Ernulfi was first witness of a confirming charter of Henry de Tracy, then Baron of Barnstaple to the Priory of St. Mary Magdalene, Barnstaple, Devonshire. He appears to have died by 1166, when his sons Jordan and Henry were in possession of his lands. He married, as her first husband, Mabel, daughter of Robert, son of Robert, Earl of Gloucester, and Hawise, daughter of Baldwin de Redvers, 1st Earl of Devon. Mabel married 2ndly, William de Soliers. As Mabel de Soliers, she confirmed in c1193-1204 a gift charter of the manors of Fleet and Ibberton, Dorsetshire from her mother, Hawise, to her son, Richard de Chambernun.\n\nThat Robert, a little known son of the Earl of Gloucester was even married, is revealed in a charter dated between June 1141 and 1161, probably before Oct 1147, in which Hawise, daughter of Earl Baldwin de Redvers, made a gift to Quarr Abbey jointly with her husband, Robert, son of the Earl of Gloucester. Robert was a natural son of Earl Robert and that he was named c1160 in a charter and is addressed in a writ from King Henry II as Castellan of Gloucester.\n\n«b»Children:«/b»\n1.) Jordan de Chambernun, m. Emma de Soligny.\n\n2.) Richard de Chambernun; in 1193-1214, he confirmed the gift of his grandmother, Hawise de Redvers, to his brother of the manors of Fleet and Ibberton, Dorsetshire.\n\n3.) Henry de Chambernun, m. Rose ____ .\n\nJordan de Champernoun used a saltire vair on his seal, per this post by Douglas Richardson at soc.genealogy.medieval. A saltire vair (a cross of alternating blue-and-white bell shapes, representing different-colored squirrel fur) is part of the later Champernoun coat of arms.","sourceList":[{"title":"Ancestry Family Trees","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"32FP-ZVZ"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1096","date":"1096","place":"Cambernon, Manche, Normandy, France, "},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1140","date":"1140","place":"Cambernon, Manche, Normandy, France","age":"44","id":"LYKM-8PM"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1157","date":"29 September 1157","place":"Evreux, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France","age":"61","id":"9CW5-J43"},{"name":"Death of Child","sources":"0","year":"1190","date":"1190","place":"Devon,  England","age":"94","id":"LYKM-8PM"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1190","date":"1190","place":", Devon, , England","age":"94"}],"parent":[{"name":"Count Jordan de Champernoun","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1070–Male","birthDate":"A+1070","@type":"Person","identifier":"GGQ9-BFR","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GGQ9-BFR/count-jordan-de-champernoun-1070","published":false},{"name":"Countess Mabel de Vernon","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1074–Female","birthDate":"A+1074","@type":"Person","identifier":"GGQ9-19V","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GGQ9-19V/countess-mabel-de-vernon-1074","published":false}],"sibling":[{"name":"Jordan Champernon","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1096–1190","birthDate":"+1096","deathDate":"+1190","age":94,"@type":"Person","identifier":"G8CR-K72","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G8CR-K72/jordan-champernon-1096-1190","pu